<section xml:id="C19.S26">
<title>Addition Theorems</title>          
<subsection xml:id="C19.S26.SS1">
<title>General Formulas</title>         
<para xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.s1">
In this subsection, and also §§19.26(ii) and 19.26(iii), we assume that <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m1">\lambda,x,y,z</Math> are positive, except that at most one of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m2">x,y,z</Math> can be 0.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="19.26.1" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E1">R_{F}\left(x+\lambda,y+\lambda,z+\lambda\right)+R_{F}\left(x+\mu,y+\mu,z+\mu \right)=R_{F}\left(x,y,z\right),</Math> where <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m3">\mu&gt;0</Math> and <Math equation-number="19.26.2" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E2">x+\mu=\lambda^{-2}\left(\sqrt{(x+\lambda)yz}+\sqrt{x(y+\lambda)(z+\lambda)} \right)^{2},</Math> with corresponding equations for <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m4">y+\mu</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m5">z+\mu</Math> obtained by permuting <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m6">x,y,z</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.s3">
Also, <Math equation-number="19.26.3" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E3">\sqrt{z}=\frac{\xi\zeta^{\prime}+\eta^{\prime}\zeta-\xi\eta^{\prime}}{\sqrt{ \xi\eta\zeta^{\prime}}+\sqrt{\xi^{\prime}\eta^{\prime}\zeta}},</Math> where <Math equation-number="19.26.4" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E4">(\xi,\eta,\zeta)=(x+\lambda,y+\lambda,z+\lambda),(\xi^{\prime},\eta^{\prime},\zeta^{\prime})=(x+\mu,y+\mu,z+\mu),</Math> with <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m7">\sqrt{x}</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m8">\sqrt{y}</Math> obtained by permuting <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m9">x</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m10">y</Math> , and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m11">z</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.s4">
(Note that <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m12">\xi\zeta^{\prime}+\eta^{\prime}\zeta-\xi\eta^{\prime}=\xi^{\prime}\zeta+\eta \zeta^{\prime}-\xi^{\prime}\eta</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.s5">
) Equivalent forms of (19.26.2) are given by <Math equation-number="19.26.5" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E5">\mu=\lambda^{-2}\left(\sqrt{xyz}+\sqrt{(x+\lambda)(y+\lambda)(z+\lambda)} \right)^{2}-\lambda-x-y-z,</Math> and <Math equation-number="19.26.6" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E6">(\lambda\mu-xy-xz-yz)^{2}=4xyz(\lambda+\mu+x+y+z)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="6" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.s6">
Also, <Math equation-number="19.26.7" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E7">R_{D}\left(x+\lambda,y+\lambda,z+\lambda\right)+R_{D}\left(x+\mu,y+\mu,z+\mu \right)=R_{D}\left(x,y,z\right)-\frac{3}{\sqrt{z(z+\lambda)(z+\mu)}},</Math> <Math equation-number="19.26.8" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E8">2\!R_{G}\left(x+\lambda,y+\lambda,z+\lambda\right)+2\!R_{G}\left(x+\mu,y+\mu,z +\mu\right)=2\!R_{G}\left(x,y,z\right)+\lambda R_{F}\left(x+\lambda,y+\lambda, z+\lambda\right)+\mu R_{F}\left(x+\mu,y+\mu,z+\mu\right)+\sqrt{\lambda+\mu+x+y +z}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="7" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.s7">
<Math equation-number="19.26.9" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E9">R_{J}\left(x+\lambda,y+\lambda,z+\lambda,p+\lambda\right)+R_{J}\left(x+\mu,y+ \mu,z+\mu,p+\mu\right)=R_{J}\left(x,y,z,p\right)-3\!R_{C}\left(\gamma-\delta, \gamma\right),</Math> where <Math equation-number="19.26.10" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E10">\gamma=p(p+\lambda)(p+\mu),\delta=(p-x)(p-y)(p-z)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="8" sentence-num-in-section="8" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.s8">
Lastly, <Math equation-number="19.26.11" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E11">R_{C}\left(x+\lambda,y+\lambda\right)+R_{C}\left(x+\mu,y+\mu\right)=R_{C}\left (x,y\right),</Math> where <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m13">\lambda&gt;0</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m14">y&gt;0</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m15">x\geq 0</Math> , and <Math equation-number="19.26.12" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E12">x+\mu=\lambda^{-2}(\sqrt{x+\lambda}y+\sqrt{x}(y+\lambda))^{2},y+\mu=(y(y+\lambda)/\lambda^{2})(\sqrt{x}+\sqrt{x+\lambda})^{2}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="9" sentence-num-in-section="9" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.s9">
Equivalent forms of (19.26.11) are given by <Math equation-number="19.26.13" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E13">R_{C}\left(\alpha^{2},\alpha^{2}-\theta\right)+R_{C}\left(\beta^{2},\beta^{2}- \theta\right)=R_{C}\left(\sigma^{2},\sigma^{2}-\theta\right), if \sigma=(\alpha\beta+\theta)/(\alpha+\beta),</Math> where <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m16">0&lt;\gamma^{2}-\theta&lt;\gamma^{2}</Math> for <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m17">\gamma=\alpha,\beta,\sigma</Math> , except that <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS1.p1.m18">\sigma^{2}-\theta</Math> can be 0, and <Math equation-number="19.26.14" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E14">(p-y)R_{C}\left(x,p\right)+(q-y)R_{C}\left(x,q\right)=(\eta-\xi)R_{C}\left(\xi ,\eta\right), if x\geq 0, y\geq 0; p,q\in\mathbb{R}\setminus\{0\},</Math> where <Math equation-number="19.26.15" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E15">(p-x)(q-x)=(y-x)^{2},\xi=y^{2}/x,\eta=pq/x,\eta-\xi=p+q-2y</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C19.S26.SS2">
<title>Case <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS2.m1">x=0</Math></title>         
<para xml:id="C19.S26.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="10" xml:id="C19.S26.SS2.p1.s1">
If <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS2.p1.m1">x=0</Math> , then <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS2.p1.m2">\lambda\mu=yz</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="11" xml:id="C19.S26.SS2.p1.s2">
For example, <Math equation-number="19.26.16" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E16">R_{F}\left(\lambda,y+\lambda,z+\lambda\right)={R_{F}\left(0,y,z\right)-R_{F} \left(\mu,y+\mu,z+\mu\right),} if \lambda\mu=yz</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="12" xml:id="C19.S26.SS2.p1.s3">
An equivalent version for <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS2.p1.m3">R_{C}</Math> is <Math equation-number="19.26.17" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E17">\sqrt{\alpha}R_{C}\left(\beta,\alpha+\beta\right)+\sqrt{\beta}R_{C}\left( \alpha,\alpha+\beta\right)=\pi/2, if \alpha,\beta\in\mathbb{C}\setminus(-\infty,0), \alpha+\beta&gt;0</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C19.S26.SS3">
<title>Duplication Formulas</title>          
<para xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="13" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="19.26.18" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E18">R_{F}\left(x,y,z\right)=2\!R_{F}\left(x+\lambda,y+\lambda,z+\lambda\right)=R_{ F}\left(\frac{x+\lambda}{4},\frac{y+\lambda}{4},\frac{z+\lambda}{4}\right),</Math> where <Math equation-number="19.26.19" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E19">\lambda=\sqrt{x}\sqrt{y}+\sqrt{y}\sqrt{z}+\sqrt{z}\sqrt{x}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="14" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="19.26.20" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E20">R_{D}\left(x,y,z\right)=2\!R_{D}\left(x+\lambda,y+\lambda,z+\lambda\right)+ \frac{3}{\sqrt{z}(z+\lambda)}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="15" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="19.26.21" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E21">2\!R_{G}\left(x,y,z\right)=4\!R_{G}\left(x+\lambda,y+\lambda,z+\lambda\right)- \lambda R_{F}\left(x,y,z\right)-\sqrt{x}-\sqrt{y}-\sqrt{z}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="16" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p1.s4">
<Math equation-number="19.26.22" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E22">R_{J}\left(x,y,z,p\right)=2\!R_{J}\left(x+\lambda,y+\lambda,z+\lambda,p+ \lambda\right)+3\!R_{C}\left(\alpha^{2},\beta^{2}\right),</Math> where <Math equation-number="19.26.23" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E23">\alpha=p(\sqrt{x}+\sqrt{y}+\sqrt{z})+\sqrt{x}\sqrt{y}\sqrt{z},\beta=\sqrt{p}(p+\lambda),\beta\pm\alpha=(\sqrt{p}\pm\sqrt{x})(\sqrt{p}\pm\sqrt{y})(\sqrt{p}\pm\sqrt{z}),\beta^{2}-\alpha^{2}=(p-x)(p-y)(p-z),</Math> either upper or lower signs being taken throughout.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="17" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p2.s1">
The equations inverse to <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p2.m1">z+\lambda=(\sqrt{z}+\sqrt{x})(\sqrt{z}+\sqrt{y})</Math> and the two other equations obtained by permuting <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p2.m2">x,y,z</Math> (see (19.26.19)) are <Math equation-number="19.26.24" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E24">z=(\xi\zeta+\eta\zeta-\xi\eta)^{2}/(4\xi\eta\zeta), if (\xi,\eta,\zeta)=(x+\lambda,y+\lambda,z+\lambda),</Math> and two similar equations obtained by exchanging <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p2.m3">z</Math> with <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p2.m4">x</Math> (and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p2.m5">\zeta</Math> with <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p2.m6">\xi</Math> ), or <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p2.m7">z</Math> with <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p2.m8">y</Math> (and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p2.m9">\zeta</Math> with <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p2.m10">\eta</Math> ).
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p3">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="18" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p3.s1">
Next, <Math equation-number="19.26.25" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E25">R_{C}\left(x,y\right)=2\!R_{C}\left(x+\lambda,y+\lambda\right), if \lambda=y+2\sqrt{x}\sqrt{y}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="19" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p3.s2">
Equivalent forms are given by (19.22.22).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="20" xml:id="C19.S26.SS3.p3.s3">
Also, <Math equation-number="19.26.26" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E26">R_{C}\left(x^{2},y^{2}\right)=R_{C}\left(a^{2},ay\right), if a=(x+y)/2, \Re x\geq 0, \Re y&gt;0,</Math> and <Math equation-number="19.26.27" mode="display" xml:id="C19.S26.E27">R_{C}\left(x^{2},x^{2}-\theta\right)=2\!R_{C}\left(s^{2},s^{2}-\theta\right), if s=x+\sqrt{x^{2}-\theta}, \theta\neq x^{2} or s^{2}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
</section>
